Git Session 1 - 07182020

Git is distributed version control system.

Repository (repo): It's an object database of the project.

files, folders : .py, .java, .js, .html, .css etc.


CLI: Command Line Interface : allows us to communicate with our operating system and apps installed on OS.

Command+Space : Terminal
Win+R : git, git-bash
-----------------------
Basic Linux commands:

cd 		: Change directory
cd / 	: go to root directory
cd ~ 	: home to home directory
cd .. 	: on folder up
. 		: current directory/folder
.. 		: upper folder 


ls: lists the files and folder in current working directory

ls -a: Show all files and folders including hidden files 

ls -l: list as a detailed list 

pwd: present/print working directory

clear : clears the screen 

history : shows the history of the commands you've used on your terminal

mkdir : make a folder

tab key: autocomplete after you write couple of letters of the folder etc.

touch : creates a file



------------------------------
Git commands:

git --version : gives you the version of your git application

You should be seeing this.
git version 2.23.0 etc.

Introduce yourself to your git application

git config --global user.name "Your name"
git config --global user.email "Your email"


Check your configuration

git config --list

Exit from app/list/etc.
exit from config list : q
ctrl+c
esc

initialize a project and create a repo
git init

new repo : .git folder (and object database inside this folder)

git status: will give you the status of your prject

git help:

git log: what happened in the project. log of the project/journal of the project etc.








git add  Filename.extension : Adding file to staging area/index tree

git add . : adds all the changes in current directory to staging area.

git add * : adds all the changes in current directory to staging area.


Committing file/taking a snapshot of the file
git commit -m "initialize the project"


SHA1 : Unique code git gives to files, folders and commits etc.


vim editor : 


vim recipe.txt

i 					: edit mode
esc					: menu mode

:wq 				: save and exit
:x 					: save and exit


What we've learned today:

Git workflow
Staging area
Repo
Version Control System



